  "body": "# Issue\r\nIt is not currently clearly defined _when_ we should call `add_validator` to process new PoW logs other than at the beginning to process the initial validator set.\r\n\r\n# Proposed Implementation\r\nCall `add_validators_from_pow_logs` right before calling `change_validators` during a validator change. Do this _before_ activating/withdrawing in an effort to optimistically induct new validators from the pow chain if possible.\r\n\r\n`validator_logs` includes _all_ deposit logs from the PoW chain up until the pow_chain_reference of the current block.\r\n\r\n```python\r\ndef add_validators_from_pow_logs(validators: List[ValidatorRecord],\r\n                                 validator_logs: List[ValidatorLog],\r\n                                 current_slot: int) -> None:\r\n    for validator_log in validator_logs:\r\n        add_validator(\r\n            validators=validators,\r\n            pubkey=validator_log.pubkey,\r\n            proof_of_possession=validator_log.proof_of_possession,\r\n            withdrawal_shard=validator_log.withdrawal_shard,\r\n            withdrawal_address=validator_log.withdrawal_address,\r\n            randao_commitment=validator_log.randao_commitment,\r\n            current_slot=current_slot\r\n        )\r\n```\r\n    ",
