    "body": "This is covered by the last part of #71:\r\n\r\n> Add a new type of SpecialObject, which consists of the entire hash-linked-list of HashChainValue logs since the previous PROCESSED_HASH_ROOT up to the POW_CHAIN_HASH_ROOT. If a valid such hash-linked-list is submitted, then we run add_validator with the given values for each record, and set PROCESSED_HASH_ROOT = POW_CHAIN_HASH_ROOT. This does mean that deposit processing is not \"automatic\"...\r\n\r\nI will grant that automatic inclusion vs manual inclusion is a significant tradeoff that could be worth discussing more. I preferred manual inclusion because it significantly simplifies the consensus complexity of beacon chain <-> PoW chain interaction, but we could potentially go either way.",
